                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.841/294: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Norway</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Swenson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-10-04T16:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 4, 1926—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>11. Telegraph Department regarding tonnage duties assessed in Norwegian ports,
                    stating whether such duties are uniform and, if not, what rates of duties are
                    assessed against American vessels as compared with rates assessed against other
                    foreign vessels and Norwegian vessels.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
